Add support for outputting diff coverage as JSON

Separate message in case of IOError/EnvormentError

Running `diff-quality` command like
`diff-quality  --violations=pylint --html-report test-results/pylint-report.html`
raises this error message `Quality tool not installed: 'pylint'`. which misleading when we `pylint` installed by html-report directory does not exist in this case `test-results`.
This PR separates the two exception to show more relavant error.

commit.message:
Handle removal of xml.etree.cElementTree in Python 3.9

In Python 3.9, xml.etree.cElementTree is gone (it has been
deprecated since 3.3). This adapts to that, retaining backwards
compatibility for Python 2 (if that's no longer considered
necessary we could of course simplify this).

Signed-off-by: Adam Williamson <awilliam@redhat.com>
